<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc0524054-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idc0524055-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This title, where footnoted in text, is title I of <ref href="/us/pl/111/148">Pub. L. 111–148</ref>, <date date="2010-03-23">Mar. 23, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/130">124 Stat. 130</ref>, which enacted this chapter and enacted, amended, and transferred numerous other sections and notes in the Code. For complete classification of title I to the Code, see Tables.</p>
</note>
